# Encounter_Design

## 1. Applies when
Combat encounters are dense, enemy composition is complex, or boss / elite / trash
configuration matters.

## 2. This document owns
Encounter types; enemy combinations; AI roles; waves; spatial pressure; combat
tempo; difficulty curve; boss phases.

## 3. This document does NOT own
Enemy raw stats (Gameplay_Systems / Unit_Design); level layout; full mission flow;
economy numbers.

## 4. Recommended chapter structure
1. Document role · 2. Encounter types · 3. Enemy combinations ·
4. AI roles & wave design · 5. Tempo & pressure · 6. Difficulty curve ·
7. Boss design · 8. TODO

## 5. Common boundaries
- Encounter vs Level — composition / count vs layout / routes.
- Encounter vs Gameplay — enemy behaviours / roles vs numeric parameters.
- Encounter vs Mission — how the fight works vs why the fight happens.

## 6. Common audit rules
- Encounter does not define enemy numbers; reference Gameplay / Unit docs.
- Boss-phase rules are not duplicated into Level or Script.
